Girl Alicia: Teacher, please tell me about medicine instead
of talking about religion!

Orphanage Priest: Alicia, it seems you're not interested in
the teachings of Terios religion... It's a shame, I believe
you have the ability to save both people's hearts and
bodies.

Girl Alicia: I have seen many people suffering from illness.
It's meaningless if their bodies die before their mental
illnesses are cured.

Orphanage Priest: Your way of thinking is like that of a
magician... Yes, someone who heard rumors about you has come
today.
Man in black: Hello, young lady.
Girl Alicia: H-Hello...

Man in black: Hahaha, are you scared of me with all these
scars?
Girl Alicia: No, does it not hurt...? I became worried.

Man in black: I've heard that you are very intelligent.
Moreover, it's admirable that you want to become a doctor
instead of a priest.

Man in black: That's right, for example, which would you
like to help, 10 people or 100 people?
Girl Alicia: I want to help both of them.

Man in black: Even if it's 100 people or 1000 people, you
would give the same answer, right? I, as an old man, have a
job of saving tens of thousands of people.
And at the same time, too.
Girl Alicia: Can you really do something like that!?

Man in black: If there are 100 people, it becomes a village.
If there are 1000 people, it becomes a town. If there are
10,000 people, it becomes a city. And if there are more than
that, it becomes a country.

Man in black: A country is a community of people, and a man
who becomes sick is not just a human doctor, but a doctor of
the nation.

Man in black: Your dream of wanting to save many people is
admirable. Remember that there are doctors who have that
same goal. I'll come again, so keep that in mind.
00_Black

Alicia grew up in the slums near Fotizona at that time. She
was not just a nobody who didn't know her parents' names or
her own name. She lived as a forgotten and invisible
existence in the empire.

Fortunately, Alicia was rescued by the monks who were
engaged in volunteer activities and given the name Alicia,
borrowing the name of a great person.

It's strange how sometimes form is born from a name. Alicia
is a typical example of that, as she underwent a drastic
transformation after being given a name. She began studying
intensely so as not to disgrace the name given to her by a
great person.

Alicia, a great person, was a renowned physician rather than
a monk, so treating people became a major goal for her.
Naturally, her upbringing in a harsh environment also had a
significant impact.

Alicia became known as a smart and beautiful girl. There
were some who had vulgar intentions, wanting to take her as
a mistress, but there were also those who recognized her
talent and offered to provide her with a suitable
environment.

However, Alicia continued to refuse and did not leave the
orphanage. It was because she was needed as a monk who saves
hearts. For her, who grew up in the slums, physical wounds
took priority over emotional wounds.

The man dressed in black appeared in such circumstances. He
taught me that there is a grand job of saving many people by
treating not just individuals, but the nation itself.

Alicia didn't give an immediate answer, but her heart was
trembling. She believed that being a transparent existence
like her former self was a sickness of the nation itself.
She believed that the job of being able to save that
sickness was a noble one.

Alicia closed the door of the orphanage with hope. And with
hope and enthusiasm, Alicia opened a new door.

Beyond the door, a man was being tortured, hanging there. It
was the dark side of the empire, the headquarters of the
Imperial Secret Service, Ishekeru. The sturdy door was
closed, and Alicia was not allowed to leave.
